The paper discusses a consensus algorithm for a distributed file system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm is based on a key-value interface, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also mentions the performance of the algorithm in terms of IOPS and latency, which relates to operating systems (cs.OS) and computer networks (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the algorithm, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
